net.sourceforge.waters.model.module

Interface SimpleComponentProxy

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<NamedProxy>, ComparableProxy<NamedProxy>, ComponentProxy, IdentifiedProxy, NamedProxy, Proxy
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleComponentElement

    public interface SimpleComponentProxy
extends ComponentProxy

    A component representing a single finite-state machine.

    Simple components are the basic way of representing the plants, specifications, and properties in a Waters module. Each simple component contains of the following information.

    Name.
    The name uniquely identifies the component in its module. It is of type IdentifierProxy, to support structured names as they may occur in parameterised structures.
    Kind.
    The kind of a component identifies it as a plants, specification, or properties. It uses the enumerative type ComponentKind.
    Graph.
    The graph shows the states and transitions of the finite-state machine representing the component. It is of type GraphProxy.
    Author:
    Robi Malik
